1
00:00:01,545 --> 00:00:06,660
When I had joined, 
that time had come,

2
00:00:06,691 --> 00:00:14,560
I remember, and it was 
in May of 1971.

3
00:00:14,806 --> 00:00:21,231
So, the Sunday feast came,
my first Sunday feast,

4
00:00:21,231 --> 00:00:26,802
which was a big deal
in ISKCON in those days.

5
00:00:26,819 --> 00:00:29,262
[The Path of Singing, 
Dancing and Feasting]

6
00:00:29,539 --> 00:00:34,961
And I remember this one devotee,
his name was Baladev,

7
00:00:34,961 --> 00:00:38,312
and it was the custom 
of the brahmacharis,

8
00:00:38,312 --> 00:00:41,663
everyone really, but especially
the brahmacharis,

9
00:00:41,663 --> 00:00:47,383
to not only shave your head on Sunday,
but what we call ‘back-shave’.

10
00:00:47,383 --> 00:00:50,102
You can shave your head,
but ‘back-shave’ means

11
00:00:50,102 --> 00:00:54,961
if you go in the other direction,
then it’s very shiny.

12
00:00:56,724 --> 00:01:00,890
So we like to do that:
back-shave our heads, tilak.

13
00:01:00,890 --> 00:01:05,907
This was the feast; an opportunity
to preach to people,

14
00:01:05,907 --> 00:01:08,805
a really joyous celebration.

15
00:01:08,805 --> 00:01:13,181
And Guru Mahārāj quotes
Vasu Gosh, the famous of

16
00:01:13,196 --> 00:01:17,817
yadi gaura nâ hoito, tabe ki hoito,
kemone dharitâm de

17
00:01:17,870 --> 00:01:22,748
râdhâr mahimâ, prema-rasa-sîmâ,
jagate jânâto ke—

18
00:01:22,748 --> 00:01:28,048
his song where he reveals
why Mahāprabhu came,

19
00:01:28,048 --> 00:01:33,927
the joyous celebration of the glories
of Rādhārāṇī and Her Kṛṣṇa-prem.

20
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:40,191
But in another śloka—
I don't know if it’s in that song,

21
00:01:40,191 --> 00:01:41,766
but in another one of his songs—
he said,

22
00:01:41,766 --> 00:01:48,526
“What kind of sādhana is this,
where by singing and dancing 
and feasting—

23
00:01:48,526 --> 00:01:54,287
that’s the path? That is our path—
singing and dancing and feasting.”

24
00:01:54,287 --> 00:01:59,434
So we heard Śrīla Prabhupād
say this so many times,

25
00:01:59,434 --> 00:02:06,088
and I always thought that it originated
with him, and perhaps it did,

26
00:02:06,088 --> 00:02:13,050
but even Vasu Gosh
in the time of Mahāprabhu,

27
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:18,911
he’s also saying how wonderful
this process is.

28
00:02:18,911 --> 00:02:23,828
So anyway, at that Sunday feast,
I remember that devotee Baladev,

29
00:02:23,828 --> 00:02:28,184
he was preaching to a guest, 
and he said,

30
00:02:28,184 --> 00:02:30,678
(as we hear, “Brahman, 
Paramātmā, Bhagavān”)

31
00:02:30,678 --> 00:02:34,770
the jñānī’s target is
the impersonal Brahman,

32
00:02:34,837 --> 00:02:39,412
the yogī’s target 
is the Paramātmā—

33
00:02:39,412 --> 00:02:42,963
the Supersoul within the heart
of every living being—

34
00:02:42,963 --> 00:02:45,778
aṇḍāntara-stha-paramāṇu-cayāntara-stham
[Bs: 5.35]

35
00:02:45,778 --> 00:02:49,416
in the heart of every atom.

36
00:02:49,416 --> 00:02:51,315
And then on that point
he said, “And the yogīs,

37
00:02:51,315 --> 00:02:57,386
sometimes we hear they’re
blazing a fire in the summer time,

38
00:02:57,386 --> 00:03:00,841
a circle of fire, and sitting in that
as an austerity.”

39
00:03:00,841 --> 00:03:07,019
Like, this type of heat.
Now, imagine when it’s hot like this,

40
00:03:07,019 --> 00:03:12,520
to blaze a fire-circle and then 
sit in the centre and meditate.

41
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:16,922
Or, he said, in the winter in Badrinath
it becomes ice-cold,

42
00:03:16,922 --> 00:03:21,869
the water freezes, and you have to poke
through the ice to get some water to bathe

43
00:03:21,869 --> 00:03:24,720
at that time, they’re meditating.

44
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:29,199
So, his point was: 
these yogīs, jñānīs,

45
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:32,572
they’re performing 
so many austerities on their path.

46
00:03:32,572 --> 00:03:37,962
And then he picked up 
a gulab-jamun, a sweet ball,

47
00:03:37,962 --> 00:03:44,015
and with the sugar juice
dripping down on his wrist

48
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:48,684
he said, “But the bhakti-yogī, 
he feasts!”

49
00:03:48,684 --> 00:03:50,731
And he threw the gulab-jamun 
in his mouth,

50
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:57,254
and went ... and juice was dripping
down his chin, and he was laughing.

51
00:03:57,254 --> 00:04:02,978
And I thought,
“I like it here! I’m stayin’”.

52
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:12,762
I thought, if somebody
can say something like that,

53
00:04:12,762 --> 00:04:15,669
that’s enough for me.

